The man was shot multiple times in a suspected armed robbery. JOHANNESBURG - Police have launched a manhunt for three suspects involved in a shooting of a 50 year old cyclist in Krugersdorp. The man was shot multiple times in a suspected armed robbery. Paramedics airlifted the man to a specialised medical facility in Johannesburg. The motive surrounding the shooting is still unknown. The police's Appel Ernst said, “Anyone with information is urged to come forward.”